        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 5:55PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 555 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Spout Spring, or near Concord, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Appomattox...
Concord...
Bent Creek...
Pamplin City...
Appomattox National Historic Park...
Stonewall...
and Hixburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
central and south central Virginia.</instruction>
